    "jays": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Blue Jays",
      "league": "MLB",
      "record": "7-13",
      "detail": "5th in AL East",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "The Blue Jays' desert debacle deepens - another flatline in Arizona, where hope goes to wither under the Chase Field lights. <strong>Corbin Carroll's eighth-inning grand slam crushed Toronto 6-2 Saturday night</strong>, capping a brutal stretch that now sits them at 7-13, dead last in the AL East, 5 games back and mired in a four-game skid after dropping both ends to the Diamondbacks and the Brewers before that. Vladimir Guerrero Jr. snagged a key out at first, but the bats mustered just 12 hits for two measly runs - no pop, no fight, as Jeff Hoffman surrendered the slam after loading the bases. No injury bulletins to blame this time; it's execution evaporating in the heat. Atkins' crew looks every bit the also-rans early, trajectory pointing toward a long summer unless the lineup awakens. <strong>Today's rubber match at 3:10 PM ET offers salvation - win it, snap the streak, steal a series from the surging Snakes, or dig the hole deeper</strong>. Jays Nation deserves better than this surrender.",
        "updated": "Updated April 19, 2026"
      },
