      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The Commanders are standing at a crossroads, armed with the No. 7 overall pick and a roster that screams for reinforcement. Last season's 5-12 finish left Dan Quinn's front office with hard choices - and mock drafts this week reveal the philosophical split defining their offseason. <strong>Multiple analysts have proposed trading back with Dallas, swapping the seventh pick for two first-rounders, a move that would let Washington target both elite receiver Makai Lemon and cornerback Jermod McCoy</strong> rather than chase one marquee prospect. The calculus is brutal: Terry McLaurin returns as the No. 1 receiver, but the cupboard beyond him is bare. Free agency has already gutted the roster - Deebo Samuel, Austin Ekeler, Marcus Mariota, Von Miller, and Zach Ertz all departed - leaving Jayden Daniels to shoulder another season with skeletal support. Some analysts argue the Commanders should go all-in with a premium running back if one falls to seven; others insist long-term building matters more than 2026 quick fixes. <strong>The draft begins next week, and this front office's next 48 hours of decision-making will define whether Washington builds or gambles</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated April 19, 2026"
